CM_ SG_ 522 ACCBrakeLightReq "Activates brake lights when ACC/ACC S&G or CMbB performs precharge.
";
CM_ SG_ 522 ACCBrakeTrqReqAck "Acknowledge of requested brake torque value. Mirror of received brake torque request.

";
CM_ SG_ 522 AWDDeclutch "The purpose is to deactivate the AWD control  ECU (DEM) during special control mode conditions (Declutch between front- and rear wheel).
(A 2 bit signal).
";
CM_ SG_ 522 LongAccOverGroundEstQF "QualityFactor for the signal LateralAcceleration.
";
CM_ SG_ 522 LongAccOverGroundEst "Estimated vehicle longitudinal acceleration over ground. For information about implementation see separate specification.
";
CM_ SG_ 522 TotWheelBrakeTrq "Momentary total vehicle brake torque (sum of all four wheels).

";
CM_ SG_ 522 VehicleStationary "The signal will be used to detect if the brakes are slowly moving.

";
CM_ SG_ 1121 KeepNetworkBCM "Inform CEM to keep CAN-HS network alive when ignition key in pos 0 , 1 or out.
";
CM_ SG_ 686 DrivingCycleOffTime "Inform about the elapsed time since the engine last was running
";
CM_ SG_ 686 TrailerConnection "Signal indicating if trailer is connected or not.
";
CM_ SG_ 686 EvapTemp "Digital value of the evap temp.
";
CM_ SG_ 686 EvapTempQF "Quality of the evaporator temp sensor value.
";
CM_ SG_ 686 EvapTempSetPt "Tells the wanted temperature of the air off the evaporator
";
CM_ SG_ 686 EnableAc "The climate system enables the AC function to use the compressor, but do not request it to run.
";
CM_ SG_ 686 ReversedGearQF "Quality factor for the signal ReversedGear.
";
CM_ SG_ 686 ReversedGear "To detect if reversing gear is in use or not for manual cars.
";
CM_ SG_ 686 ClimHighIdleSpeedReq "Request a higher engine idle speed
";
CM_ SG_ 686 IndicationIlluminationCmd "Out signal to other Function Areas. Desides the brightness of the indication illumination when a system is in function and/or out of function.


";
CM_ SG_ 686 FuelHatchPopUp "Informs if the fuel hatch is open or not. It is used to enable, inhibit or abort the leakage testing.

";
CM_ SG_ 686 CarMode "Information about which Carmode the vehicle is in i.e. Normal, factory etc.
";
CM_ SG_ 653 FuelPumpStatus "Diagnostic status of the fuel pump.
";
CM_ SG_ 653 CMbBAllowedByMonitor "Dependability signal. Forces the CADS Mode Manager to immediately cancel CMbB for the rest of the driving cycle.

";
CM_ SG_ 653 ACCAllowedByMonitor "Dependability signal. 'ACC denied by monitor' forces the CADS Mode Manager to immediately cancel ACC for the rest of the driving cycle.

";
CM_ SG_ 653 ParkingBrakeActive "Information about Parking brake status, activated or not activated.
IVDC name:   Ssc_B_PrkBrkActv
";
CM_ SG_ 653 RecDegree "The recirculation flap position, range 0..100%
";
CM_ SG_ 653 AirFlow "Tells the fanspeed of the climate fan, range 0..6350 rpm
";
CM_ SG_ 1894 TesterPhysicalReqDEM "Refer to 'Generic Global Diagnostic Specification' (VCC doc. no. 31810161).
";
CM_ SG_ 1072 EvapTempSetPtInfo "Tells the used set point temperature of the air off the evaporator
";
CM_ SG_ 1072 KeepNetworkECM "Restarts the KeepNetAliveTimer in the master ECU.
";
CM_ SG_ 1072 ECMChecksumResponse "Response to the checksum request from the PJB (Software Security). The PJB must receive a response within 10 sec after a request has been issued in CEM.
";
CM_ SG_ 1072 EngineWarningInd "Engine warning information to be displayed in DIM (text and amber warning lamp). Req. on Rx ECU: DIM has to bound amber lamp to text id.Req. on Tx ECU: ECM must synchronize signal with MIL-lamp status to control if the signal shall be sent or not.
";
CM_ SG_ 1072 DieselFilterWarmer "Gives infomation if the diesel filter warmer shall be active or not.
";
CM_ SG_ 1072 ACPressureHighsideQF "Quality factor to signal ACPressureHighside
";
CM_ SG_ 1072 ACPressureHighside "To estimate (stationary) torque, so that CCM can inform ECM
";
CM_ SG_ 1072 Econometer "The econometer signal is used to calculate accumulated and instantaneous fuel consuption.The signal contains the accumulated number of fuel flow pulses modulus 256 during the last driving cycle; the signal value shall be reset to 0 at every ignition on.
";
CM_ SG_ 1072 TotAxleFrictionTrq "Actual total axle torque to overcame friction effects.This is a calculated value incl.  engine, transmission, final gear and temp. effects.

";
CM_ SG_ 1072 TotAxleFrictionTrqQF "Quality factor for the signal TotAxleFrictionTrq.

";
CM_ SG_ 555 KickDown "Information that a driver action shall lead to gear down shift (kick-down). Calculated from accelerator pedal position.


IVDC name:  VscDifApif_B_KickDown
";
CM_ SG_ 555 AvailableCrankShaftTrqMax "The maximum possible Crank Shaft Torque assuming wide open throttle at the current engine speed and maximum ISG (integrated starter generator) torque boost if fitted. It does not include inertia or turbo transient over-boost
";
CM_ SG_ 555 ClutchPedalPressed "Clutch pedal position measured as analog value. The signal shall reflect the raw sensor value.
";
CM_ SG_ 555 CCActive "Dependability signal ('CCA'). Indicated that cruise control is active. The signal is contained in the group RequestedThrottleGrp (RTA, CCO, CCA).
IVDC name:   VscDeScl_D_CcMode
";
CM_ SG_ 555 CCMode "Controls the ACC mode.

";
CM_ SG_ 555 CCOverridden "Dependability signal (CCO). Indicated that cruise control is overridden (ECM decision). Torque required by driver is larger than CC torque request. The signal is contained in the group RequestedThrottleGrp (RTA, CCO, CCA).
";
CM_ SG_ 555 ACCActiveAllowed "Primary ON/OFF signal for ACC.


";
CM_ SG_ 555 IdleSpeed "Current idle speed
";
CM_ SG_ 1042 AmbientAirPressureQF "Quality factor for the signal AmbientAirPressure.
";
CM_ SG_ 1042 CCResumeReq "Indicates if the Resume Button is pressed.

";
CM_ SG_ 1042 TimeGapMinus "Driver request to decrease one step in ACC time gap, indicates button activated.

";
CM_ SG_ 1042 TimeGapPlus "Driver request to increase one step in ACC time gap, indicates button activated.

";
CM_ SG_ 1042 MaxEngineBrakeReached "Indicates that maximum achievable engine brake has been reached.

";
CM_ SG_ 1042 CCSetSpeed "Indicates the set speed to the cruise control regulator and other stakeholders.



IVDC name:    VscDeScl_V_CcLongReq

";
CM_ SG_ 1042 TM_TerrainMode "This signal indicates the terrain mode that the EMS is currently in.
";
CM_ SG_ 1042 TM_TerrainModeChangeStatus "Availability of EMS to change from current terrain mode into another mode (not including rock crawl mode) This signal replaces EMS_ModeGroupStatus for L319 HTFB
";
CM_ SG_ 1042 AvailableCurrentAtIdling "This signal is the available current from the alternator at idlespeed.
";
CM_ SG_ 1042 AmbientTemp "Ambient air temperature
";
CM_ SG_ 1042 AmbientTempQF "Quality factor for the signal AmbientTemp.
";
CM_ SG_ 1042 AmbientAirPressure "The ambient air pressure measured by the pressure sensor.
";
CM_ SG_ 1081 EPBBrakeLightReq "EPB activation of rear brake lamps during dynamic EPB braking
";
