CM_ SG_ 294 SteeringAngleCRShortFilt "To inform power steering about actual steering angle change rate of the steering wheel. The value is an absolute value.
";
CM_ SG_ 294 SteeringAngleStatus "To inform BCM about the status of the calculations used for the signals SteeringAngle and SteeringAngleCR.
";
CM_ SG_ 294 SteeringAngleCS "To inform BCM about if the data in the signals SteeringAngle and SteeringAngleCR is correct or not.
";
CM_ SG_ 294 SteeringAngleCounter "To inform BCM that the signal SteeringAngle value (sent in the same frame) is a new value and also to be able to identify if a value is missing.

";
CM_ SG_ 294 SteeringAngleCRSign "When the vehicle is making a left turn this signal is supposed to show positive numbers. Unfiltered and offset compensated plausibility check.
";
CM_ SG_ 294 SteeringAngleSign "To inform BCM about actual steering angle direction, from the centre position of the steering wheel. Used in the AYC-function calculations. The absolute steering wheel angle is supplied in the signal SteeringAngle.
";
CM_ SG_ 457 CMbBEBASensReq "CMbB request to brake system for a particular sensitivity of the Emergency Brake Assist (EBA) function. The request indicates that one of four parameter settings for EBA shall be selected.

";
CM_ SG_ 457 CMbBBrakePrechargeReq "CMbB request to brake system for a pre-charge activation (using the active booster or the pump). Pre-charge level 1 corresponds to approximately 6 bar and level 2 corresponds to approximately 12 bar.

";
CM_ SG_ 457 CMbBBrakeTrqReq "Controls the brake system CMbB braking. Sum of all four wheel brake torques.

";
CM_ SG_ 457 CMbBReqCS "Dependability concept checksum.

";
CM_ SG_ 457 CMbBAllowed "Dependability signal. 'CMbB not allowed' terminates immediately all CMbB activation (enter CMbB Denied Mode) for the rest of the driving cycle.


";
CM_ SG_ 457 CMbBEngineBrakeReqCounter "Dependability concept counter.


";
CM_ SG_ 457 CMbBEngineBrakeReq "CMbB request to powertrain indicating that engine torque shall immediately be reduced to a minimum. This corresponds to a torque level where the accelerator pedal would have been completely  released at the same moment in time.

";
CM_ SG_ 457 CMbBEngineBrakeReqInv "Dependability concept signal, inverse of CMbBEngineBrakeReq

";
CM_ SG_ 457 ACCMaxAccelerationReq "Main control signal for ACC Engine Control. Puts a limit on the Cruise Controller acceleration. Normal operating range -3..+2 m/s^2.

";
CM_ SG_ 457 ACCCancel "Forces the Cruise Control Manager to immediately cancel ACC. Manual set and resume allowed.

";
CM_ SG_ 457 ACCDenied "Forces the Cruise Control Manager to immediately cancel ACC for the rest of the current driving cycle.

";
CM_ SG_ 457 CMbBReqCounter "Dependability concept counter.

";
